)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Types.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm\">EvalTerm</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"A type that can be used when constructing expression for the `TermInfo`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Types.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm.typeExpr","kind":"def","line":44,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm.typeExpr","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Types.lean#L44-L44"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">abbrev</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Types.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm.evalTerm\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">EvalTerm</span>.<span class=\"name\">evalTerm</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\">self</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Types.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm\">EvalTerm</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Meta/Defs.html#Lean.Syntax.Term\">Term</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">TermElabM</a> (<span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Direct evaluation of `Term` syntax, avoiding term elaboration.\nInstances should use `throwUnsupportedSyntax` to signal that the syntax is not recognized.\nInstances shouldn't generally throw other exceptions.\n\nEvaluation is allowed to imagine that certain coercions are implicitly inserted.\nFor example, the `Option Int` instance is allowed to recognize `1` as an `Option Int`\neven though term elaboration would fail here. This allowance should be used lightly,\nsince generally `EvalTerm` is used as the fast path, and when using the `EvalExpr`\nbackup, such expressions will no longer be recognized.\n\nImplementations should add `TermInfo` when the info is enabled.\nThe `Expr` return value is to support constructing such expressions in combinators.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Types.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm.evalTerm","kind":"def","line":40,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm.evalTerm","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Types.lean#L40-L40"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Types.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm.mk\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">EvalTerm</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>} → <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Meta/Defs.html#Lean.Syntax.Term\">Lean.Term</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">Lean.Elab.TermElabM</a> (<span class=\"fn\">α</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a>)</span>)</span> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Lean.Expr</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Types.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm\">Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Types.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm.mk","kind":"ctor","line":22,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Types.lean#L22-L44"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">class</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Types.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">EvalTerm</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Class for evaluation of `Term` syntax directly to a runtime value.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Types.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm","kind":"class","line":22,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.EvalTerm","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Types.lean#L22-L44"}}],"imports":["Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM","Lean.Parser.Term"],"instances":[],"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.Types"}